Definition: the trait of acting unpredictably and more from whim or caprice than from reason or judgment
Example: I despair at the flightiness and whimsicality of my memory
Synonyms: adj, all, frivolous, flighty, arbitrariness, arbitrary, whimsicality, whimsical, whimsy, whimsey, capriciousness, capricious, irresponsibility, the, trait, of, acting, unpredictably, and, more, from, whim, or, caprice, than, reason, judgment, I, despair, at, my, memory
Category: noun.attribute
